opendial.bn.distribs

Interface ProbDistribution

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DiscreteDistribution, IndependentProbDistribution
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CategoricalTable, ConditionalCategoricalTable, ConditionalDistribution, ContinuousDistribution, DeterministicDistribution, EmpiricalDistribution, EquivalenceDistribution, IncrementalDistribution, MarginalEmpiricalDistribution, OutputDistribution, RuleDistribution

    public interface ProbDistribution
    Generic probability distribution of the type (PX1,...Xn | Y1,...Yn). The distribution may be discrete or continuous.
    Version:
    $Date:: 2014-02-04 09:51:48 #$
    Author:
    Pierre Lison (plison@ifi.uio.no)

      • getPosterior

        IndependentProbDistribution getPosterior(Assignment condition)
                                         throws DialException
        Returns the probability table for the head variables, given the conditional assignment given as argument. This method requires a full assignment of values to the conditional variables of the current distribution.

        If a head variable has a continuous range, the values defined in the table are based on a discretisation procedure which creates a sequence of buckets, each with an approximatively similar probability mass.

        Parameters:
        condition - the assignment for the conditional variable
        Returns:
        the resulting probability table
        Throws:
        DialException
